Human: <p>I received a phishing text message that pretended to be my bank. It had a link that went to a site that redirect to the following script:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;html&gt;&lt;script language="javascript"&gt;var page = "Login.php?sslchannel=true&amp;sessionid=XXX”; top.location = page; &lt;/script&gt;&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>When I did a <code>wget</code> on that page with the rest of the full url it ran the following script:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
    window.googleJavaScriptRedirect = 1
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
    var n = {
        navigateTo: function(b, a, d) {
            if (b != a &amp;&amp; b.google) {
                if (b.google.r) {
                    b.google.r = 0;
                    b.location.href = d;
                    a.location.replace("about:blank");
                }
            } else {
                a.location.replace(d);
            }
        }
    };
    n.navigateTo(window.parent, window, "https://www.banksite.com/");
&lt;/script&gt;&lt;noscript&gt;&lt;META http-equiv="refresh" content="0;URL='https://www.banksite.com/'"&gt;&lt;/noscript&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>From a technical perspective, I'm trying to figure out what this phishing text could have done in the worst case scenario.</p>


